basic_profile_info.description: Dis-moi ce que tu manges, je te dirai qui tu es. 😀😉

reviews.name: Domino's Pizza
reviews.text: always lives up to its name

reviews.name: Subway
reviews.text: wrong bread

reviews.name: Subway
reviews.text: Absolutely pathetic. This outlet is by far the worst and NOBODY SHOULD EVER ORDER FROM HERE. The must be illiterate to completely mess up my order for third time. All unwanted items were added and items that I wanted were all missing. Total frauds here in this outlet. Ordered four subs and they contained cabbage, pickles, jalapeños and cucumbers when I clesrly excluded them. Only mayonnaise was there and all the 7 other sauces which I had added were missing. Even the bread was wrong.

reviews.name: The ThickShake Factory
reviews.text: Absolutely delectable super thick shakes are served here! The shakes are so thick that they may have to be eaten with a spoon. The texture, flavour and toppings perfectly complement each other and the subsequent result is heavenly. My personal favourites are the choco brownie crumble, strawbanana, ice cream Oreo, fererro hazelnut, and cold coffee indulgence thicksakes

reviews.name: Firangi Bake
reviews.text: Simply overpriced for the food provided. I truly appreciate the concept of fusion cuisine but there's i don't understand what this restaurant served. The four beans quesadilla was too saucy and oily and the flavour was ruined by the former, and the texture by the latter.  The packaging inside the attractive outer box was completely drenched in oil to my utter disappointment. The Bombay masala quesadilla was just filled with potatos and was bland while the the other was too saucy. There's barely any hint of Mexican flavour in the quesadillas. Furthermore, tue quesadillas are overpriced at 210 apiece. Terribly disappointed and won't recommend anyone to visit this place.

reviews.name: Domino's Pizza
reviews.text: Dominos continues to lives up to the legacy of its name and never ceases to please. A tremendous improvement in both , the taste and quality of the pizzas can be attributed to the policy changes made by the new CEO (India). The new hand tossed crust is very buttery and soft, askin to its fresh pan counterpart. The cheese burst crust is my personal favorite; and yes "cheese burst" can be literally interpreted as cheese oozes from the base. With the introduction of everyday value offers and a reduction in GST, premium pizzas have become far more affordable. Every pizza and side in the menu is unique and delectable. The staff on the other hand, in this particular outlet and indifferent and rude. I was served the pizza 30 minutes after constantly nagging them. The staff need to be trained to be professional, efficient and polite.

reviews.name: Pizza Hut
reviews.text: Despite being part of an old and reputed chain and having the legacy of being the best pizza chain in the world, this outlet MUST be avoided at all costs. The overloaded big pizzas are sizeable but have soggy crusts. Their BOGO offers are very deceiving and are nothing more than a carefully construed marketing strategy to Rob customers of their money. The pan pizzas have very little cheese, stale toppings and oily crusts.  2 of such pizzas for ₹600 is nothing less than daylight robbery; and are not even worth one slice of ots dominos counterparts.

reviews.name: Tovo
reviews.text: best American food in the vicinity. The taste and quality are remarkably good. The burgers are amongst the best you'd get in chennai. veggie tovo slate is my all time favourite. It's really intriguing as you can use your creatively in choosing the infusions , sauces and toppings(mind, everything is excellent). The buns are oh so soft and the fillings overflow that it's hard to eat it. The rice is also excellent. The cottage cheese steak is another one of my favourites and is always cooked the way I ask, to perfection. There are no words to express the heavenly taste of the food served on tovo. EVERY penny you pay is well accounted for in terms of quality and taste, which is unparalleled. A place that MUST be visited

reviews.name: Fruit Shop On Greams Road
reviews.text: As a customer of fruit shop for over a decade, I have never ceased to be pleased by the wonderful shakes(I hate juices) and desserts. The unwavering taste at reasonable prices make me visting this joint over and over again. My personal favourite here , is Kolkofe. It's amongst the best and cheapest cold coffees I've had in Chennai(CCD's in yuck) with the perfect proportion and flavour. That apart every other shake is excellent.

reviews.name: Tibbs Frankie
reviews.text: THE BEST stiffed rolls in chennai. Their fillings are absolutely amazing. I've tried every variant with each being unique and delicious in its own way. Honestly, Frankie has no close alternatives or competitors nearby taking into consideration the taste and pricing. My personal favourites are tawa paneer and tawa Gobi Frankies. Can fill you up for 50 bucks. Totally deserves 5/5 and this branch is the best .

reviews.name: The Kati Roll Shop
reviews.text: below average rolls. The size is decent but the fillings are bad especially for the price. Frankie and bayleaf OTG are way better and offer better value for money. these are easily the worst Kati rolls I've had in chennai. The paneer, Malai paneer and cheese and mayo​ Kati rolls are horrible. The vegetable Manchurian Kati roll is the only thing that's decent. I paid ₹ 500 for 4 Kathi rolls. this place is to be avoided at all costs if you are a vegetarian. Extra cheese for ₹20 in almost non-existent. The sauces used in the filling are horrible

reviews.name: Hot Chips
reviews.text: As one one of the few hot chips outlets that still uphold their quality, it was the place where I had lunch every Sunday after my caching classes for over a year. Their south Indian dishes and North Indian sides are noteworthy. Thiet Chaat items are are quite good. However, they're pizzas and sandwiches are atrocious and must never be ordered. They have offer self service as well as an AC restaurant, and the latter is better even though it's a bit cramped. Their Bombay meals is my favorite combo. It offers a combination of may dishes like fried rice, noodles, naan, Gobi Manchurian, paneer heavy, curd Rice, a dessert, a sweet and soup for 180 bucks(a steal). Parking may be a problem.

reviews.name: Vishranthi
reviews.text: I've known this place for a long time and have visited many I time when I was a kid. It used to have a nice cozy ambience and great food. After a renovation half a decade back, they made it into a self-service joint without air conditioning and poor ambience. The taste has also significantly reduced and the menu cut short. 15 years back most of the restaurants in Besant nagar that we see today didn't exist and this was one of my favourite places. I loved their milkshakes but unfortunately they don't serve them anymore. Sadly, it's a very ordinary joint today that serves a few south Indian and even fewet north@ Indian dishes. Not the best place to visit but it's very economic.

reviews.name: AB's - Absolute Barbecues
reviews.text: I'm finally reviewing this place after 5 visits. The staff is impeccably warm and caring. They will quite literally be at your command. Being a vegetarian, I was quite disappointed with the starters. The only good starters on the grill were the paneer skewers(which was oh so soft) and the mushroom. The fruit kebabs were horrible and it would really be good if more veg grills could be added like cauliflower, veg sheek kebab and veggies like onions, tomatoes, capsicum etc in between paneer and mushroom grills. The American cheese potato was the best starter in my opinion. The complimentary drinks are good , but the varieties could be increased. The main course was wonderful I I really loved the rotis, butter naans and the peas masala. The pasta was annoyingly sweet and tasted bad. The wish grill was excellent I loved experimenting new combinations on every visit. The desserts are amazing, especially the cold stone ice cream. Overall, I had a pleasant experience but it would be really appreciable if AB's didnt give the special occasion cake in the end when we're stuffed and instead give it in the beginning(to avoid wastage).

reviews.name: Brownie Heaven
reviews.text: I finally ordered from this place after tonnes of good reviews. My school's commerce club organised an interview with the owner of Brownie heaven (who is an alumunus of my school) ,and my friend who had interviewed him also told me that the brownies tasted amazing. All this hype only added to my expectations of brownie heaven. So I finally ordered from this outlet through swiggy. The brownies were delivered warm in an attractive sealed box. When i finally tasted the brownies I was very disappointed.

reviews.name: AB's - Absolute Barbecues
reviews.text: AB's stands true to it's high rating. It's very rare to see such a warm,courteous and caring staff I'm India and they will certainly make you feel very welcome and comfortable. The food is excellent and there's certainly no doubt about that, from numerous other reviews. The starters and desserts are amazing even though the main course is slightly limited. However I was most impressed with their customer(satisfaction) oriented approach and their service gives a whole new meaning to the term.

reviews.name: Adyar Treat Restaurant
reviews.text: After a terribly nightmarish experience, I've vowed never to eat here. I ordered online through the swiggy app and the food was delivered in thirty minutes. I've visited this place on the past and have had a few pleasant experiences (+2.5,)However when I received my order I was absolutely shocked. I Had ordered Gobi Peshawari and what I received was a complete mess. It was a semi-solid mixture of peas, dal(seriously) with hardly any cauliflower and the cauliflower pieces were 1/15th of their normally served counterparts(90% dal). Next , when I opened the paneer tikka box I was shocked again. 1/5th pf the containet was filled with water mixed with some oil(yes water!!!) The paneer tikka wasn't properly cooked either and mixed with the water, it tasted horrible. The rotis where made well but I can't really eat it plain. I would never recommend anyone to eat here(atleast delivery). In the restaurant their service is so sluggish that I've got irritated on more than one occasion. But this experience was the worst ever!!!

reviews.name: Hot Chips
reviews.text: Located right near the Thiruvanmiyur junction, this place is not really hard to find. Being very close to my house I've visited this outlet dozens of times , but what instigated me to write this review was yet another terrible experience from this place. I would advice anybody to avoid this place at all costs as is completely worthless on terms of time and money. They have two options namely self service without aircon and an air-conditioned restaurant. The former is fast but has no seating arrangement and the latter is very slow in terms of service. The staff here is exceptionally rude so don't expect a good service. The ambience is nothing to brag about either, and the place isnt usually very crowded. The price of the food is completely disproportionate to the quality, taste and quantity. Their north Indian main courses are primarly constituted by oil and spice and the portions are meagre. The south Indian items taste alright the the price and quantity don't really match. I'd prefer sangeeta any day. Their chaats are okay but not too great. Parking can be a huge problem as they have NO 4 wheeler parking and parking nearby can be cumbersome. But I would like to reiterate that their staff is very uncooperative and rude which completely ruins your dining experience. All said, I would give this nightmarish outlet the lowest permissible rating.

reviews.name: Goli Vada Pav No. 1
reviews.text: Despite the relatively high ratings, I was quite disappointed with some of their vada pav variants.

reviews.name: Bharani Veg
reviews.text: ordered food home from this place a couple of times. food is really mediocre and not worth the price at all. The paneer 65 was too oily and the paneer wasn't fesh. Chili paratha was okay but oily as well. chaats are fine but i'd like to reinstate that the food is disproportionately priced for the poor taste and quality.  This place used to be good a decade back but sadly, it has declined. The only things that are okay are the snacks like bajji, bonda etc. It'd be better to go to hot chips even though the difference isn't that great.

reviews.name: Cafe Coffee Day
reviews.text: Ordered via Swiggy from CCD Perungudi@ 50℅ off . I guess all branches of CCD aren't uniform in preparing coffee, from my experience at least. the hot gourmet cocoa was excellent ,thick and frothy with chocolate. Reminds me of the hot chocolate in US Starbucks. the pastries were also excellent though I personally didn't like the hazelnut karat pastry much, but my friends loved it(tasted more like banana walnut brownie and didn't suit the name; apparently good nevertheless). The gourmet cocoa was the best though, making me feel nostalgic😘. I've tried all the pastries here and they're excellent. I haven't tried snacks at this outlet but in some others they're disgusting so my review is solely based on what I ordered. With 50% off the bill was really less and came only upto 316 with 4 pastries and 1 chocolica, all being almost equal in cost. So it's better to order from CCD through swiggy I guess..

reviews.name: Eagle Boys Pizza
reviews.text: I've ordered from here a few times after seeing the good reviews, but I've only felt varying degrees of disappointment after every order.  To go straight to the point, the pizzas are not up to the mark or worth the price at all. The crust is really bad and the most displeasing attribute. Its a bit hard, not soft or crunchy kinda more like the bases you'd get in a local bakery. Being an international joint and considering the pricing, this certainty wasn't what i expected. At first I thought them i'd caught them on a wrong day but the same poor taste and quality continued to ensue. The toppings are also very average but not bad. The cheese they use here is of average to poor quality and sauces are also plain and bland; nothing special or nothing to brag.  Sorry to say , but the sides are outright pathetic especially the cheesy garlic scroll. I've gone only once to the restaurant, and swore never to go again. It was poorly maintained with a poor ambience and was full of flies. I guess the pricing is similar to Domino's and i'd prefer the latter any day. Hence I would recommend you to go to Domino's or pizza hut rather than this place as they are all closely located anyway and better by a colossal gap with wonderful,distinct flavours. The pizzas taste like slightly upgraded adyar bakery pizzas and I would have given a better rating if they were priced similarly as well.

reviews.name: Ashvita Nirvana
reviews.text: Ordered from Ashvita Nirvana through swiggy this time. Unwavering quality and taste are trademark attributes of this joint; never ceases to impress. I ordered vegetable lasagne and butter tossed pasta with olives(penne). The lasagne was excellent and the portion was huge, more than what an average person can have and had the right amount of cheese this time. The pasta was also very good. The pasta was soft and buttery with a Mediterranean flavour due to the generous amount of green olives. There were lots of vegetables and I really loved it. I couldn't have the Monster shake this time because it was a delivery order. The last thing I'd like to mention is the wonderful packaging. Ashvita nirvana packed the food in eco friendly cartons and put it inside an elaborately hand crafted paper bag. Hats off for their care and concern for the environment.

reviews.name: Tasty Bakes
reviews.text: Nice small place near my house and I've probably visited it hundreds of times. The cakes , pizzas, burgers and puffs are simply delicious 😘. When you approach the bakery the aroma of freshly baking cakes wafts through the air luring you towards it. Tiny but an all time favourite since childhood. If u pass by don't fail to drop in!!

reviews.name: Aasife & Brothers Biriyani Cen...
reviews.text: This place is really close to my house hence I've ordered a few times out of curiosity seeing the poor rating. True to the ratings this place doesn't cease to disgust me thoroughly. Ordered Singapore fried noodles from here and the package contained a mixture of rice and noodles. It has a good ambience but the food is disgusting. They literally pour gallons of oil in the food. The taste is okay but it certainly isn't healthy. The cost is totally not worth the food they provide. The foodr is full of oil, color , excessive salt and sauces. Do not order from here, period. It lives up to its poor rating

reviews.name: Domino's Pizza
reviews.text: Whats more to say, Domnino's is Dominos! They've recently shifted from their previous cramped quarters to a larger building a couple hundred metres away. The taste and consistency domino's offers is completely unparalleled. out of the numerous domino's pizza joints i've visited, their uniformity and exuberant taste has never ceased to overwhelm me. furthermore domino's Inida's taste is slowly moving towards that of the original American domino's joints. The adyar joint is quite spacious with two stories. the staff need to learn to attend the customers better and learn to be MORE friendly. When i visited last week, they were quite indifferent and callous. that aside, domino's pizza  completely stopped their famous buy one get one free offers for a while now, and considering that Papa Johns and Pizza hut constantly offering the aforementioned, i'd prefer the latter. yet domino's pizza's taste is the best but pizza hut and papa johns are catching up and domino's needs to give more lucrative offers. My favourite pizzas are country special, double  cheese margher, cloud 9 and veg extravaganza. the new quattro Formaggi burst is good,but after its launch domino's has made cheeseburst. "cheeseles"burst. Last but not the least domino's staff at this joint are profound liars. Whenever you order  medium or regular pizza they've begun to lie that the normal base(classic hand tossed base) isnt't available and only the pan base fr which you have to pay extra is available. Once, when I asked them to cancel the order they immediately told me that the normal crust was available. Such behaviour is thoroughly disgusting and seriously devalued my trust and goodwill on domino's pizza, Adyar. However this behaviour is exclusive to this joint and the Thiruvanmiyur joint. Otherwise Domino's stands up to its name

reviews.name: WOSS - World of Sub's & Salad's
reviews.text: Small joint in front of Spencer's , Ghandi Nagar. It's near my school and perfect for a quick evening snack. The subs and burgers are really good  I've also ordered many times from here through swiggy as they have buy one get one free offers a few times a year. They use whole wheat bread and lots of fresh cut veggies so it's a quintessential healthy snack. The salads are okay but I'm not really fond of them. But the joint is economic and ideal for a healthy snack. I love the corn and paneer burger though.

reviews.name: Adyar Bakery
reviews.text: Sadly adyar bakery is on the steady decline in terms of quality and quantity.I'm hardly visiting this place nowadays to save myself from imminent and inevitable disappointment that never ceases to accompany me after a visit. They never fail to hike the prices on time however the quality is getting worse;. The cakes are getting harder and several products have ceased to exist. Their variety has also fallen. The snacks are okay but I would prefer CKs bakery any time over it as it's nearby as well. The chaars are okay. However I'm sad that such an excellent and well reputed bakery is getting this bad

reviews.name: Tibbs Frankie
reviews.text: An excellent street food joint and tastes extraordinarily similar to the original Bombay tibbs Frankie. The frankies and wheat and Maida rotis filled with onions and and fillings of choice. They are extremely popular and the place gets ridiculously crowded on the evenings and often runs out fast. Both the veg and non veg frankies are brilliant. The tawa paneer and Gobi Manchurian frankies are my personal favourites. I've eaten here several times maybe a couple hundreds in the last five years but I never get bored and crave for more sooner or later. The prices have barely increased in the last decade inline other joints. It's a must try !!

reviews.name: CK's Bakery
reviews.text: Excellent place for cakes and sandwiches. Their sandwiches are simply brilliant. The Paninis and subs are also really good. The cheese and mayo they use is really yummy and it is one of the best bakeries here, easily surpassing adyar bakery in terms of tatse and quality. The cakes and puddings are excellent. The choco truffle and red velvet cakes so tasty and soft. The best part is that CKs bakery is also very economic. I love ordering online here but I don't why CKs bakery doesn't have cakes and puddings in its online menu in Swiggy.

reviews.name: Cafe Coffee Day
reviews.text: Ordered a couple of times from here through home delivery. Never ceased to thoroughly disappoint me to the core. The quantity of the food is disgustingly poor and the never fail to flaunt themselves as a prestigious chain at every given opportunity. It is absolutely ridiculous. The Cutlet costs 100 bucks and is supposed to have 2 pieces. However they served only 1 piece and it was cold and tasted like a ready to fry packeted Cutlet, in fact the latter tastes better. By far!!!. The cappuccino was the only thing that was worth having. Only the beverages are okay in this place, everything else in absolute garbage and not worth a dime. I got a 50% off compounded with a ,RS 50 off on Swiggy and still it was worthless. The choco indulgence pastry was okay but hard and not worth the price. Please don't have the wraps and burgers . They will literally give you a dry bun with an uncooked patty with nothing inside except beetroot and whatever vegetables they have . there's no cheese and it's disgusting . Only have beverages and desserts here.

reviews.name: Aroma Bakes
reviews.text: A small bakery near my school and mostly haunted by school students because of its close proximity to many schools in the area. The quality of the food is below average and certainly not healthy, the fried foods and sandwiches are soggy, stale and oily, since they don't have a kitchen the food is brought in from somewhere else. The cakes are good but the taste and quality are highly inconsistent. A few events made me stop visiting this place all together. Once I found a cockroach in the mousse and even though it was replaces it only increases my weariness with the place. The second time I had a cake which was hard and I presume stale and suffered form a bad case of food poisoning.

reviews.name: Animal Kingdom
reviews.text: Went here for dinner with my friend after hearing a lot good reviews by word and online. Firstly the place is pretty secluded and the entrance to the passage which leads to the back of the building is narrow. Secondly, Gmaps shows that animal kingdom is located in the same place as rain forest and that was pretty confusing as they are located 50m apart. Lastly the restaurant is in the fourth floor and the lift may not always work.

reviews.name: CK's Bakery
reviews.text: best place in the vicinity for good quality pastries, cakes and sandwiches. Their cakes and puddings are really tasty not to mention super economic. Their sandwiches and paninis are delicacies extraordinaire and must me tried especially the paneer tikka ones. The joint is pretty small and can get cramped but is perfect for takeaways and online orders through zomato and weight.

reviews.name: Amirtha Ice Creams
reviews.text: Excellent place for softy cones, super cheap and tasty. Perfect while walking past on a hot day. On the contrary, the packed ice creams are really bad and a bit overpriced for their quality. Never buy ice creams here if there's a power cut cuz they have no backup!!😐

reviews.name: Jalpaan
reviews.text: One of the best buffet restaurants in and around adyar for vegetarians. The buffet menu is quite extensive with an array of starters brought to the table. I liked the sheek kebab and the panner tikka the most . They give enough starters to make you full so make sure you're super hungry before you go. They have a live chat and pasta counter on the left side while the mains are served on the right, the pasta was a bit bland and the chaats were good. The mains are quite good with fried  rice, pulao, noodles and various side dishes. The bread is brought to the table as and when requested. The desserts are damn good and they always have a halwa in the counter. The mousse nd cakes are good too. The only con is that the ice creams arw limited and brought to the table unlike other buffet restaurant. The amience is definitely enthralling and quite exquisite not to mention the grand plates and goblets. The lunch buffet on weekdays is pretty economic. On weekends ordering separately from the menu is a good choice as well.

reviews.name: Food Out
reviews.text: Pretty decent place which offers takeaway late in the night and its extremely convinient for me because of its close proximity to my place. The starters and north Indian items are quite good. The chinese items like fried rice and noodles are oily and are quite disappointing. It's perfect for a takeaway late in the night . Their paneer tikka and chilli Gobi are dman good. Their pricing is okay but considering that they aren't a restaurant it's a but on the higher side for the food they provide. One major lacuna is that the taste and texture of dishes served here aren't consistent - sometimes they're exceptionally good while they are pretty bad on others especially the non vegetarian gravies.

reviews.name: Domino's Pizza
reviews.text: Dominos pizza is undoubtedly the all time favorite pizza joint. Innovation and variety have no bounds with kinda makes me addicted to this place😊 . This joint is quite close to my place; most of the time I just order a home delivery while I also occasionally drop by as well. The taste and flavours are undoubtedly the best. I just love the cheese and toppings. Dominos keeps introducing new items in its menu so there is no scope for getting bored. The cheese burst upgrade is the best while the new Quattro Formaggi burst osnt far behind. Out of all the American pizza joints dominos is the pioneer of innovation. Both pizza hut and Papa John's copied dominos pizza by naming them differently(not that I complain , variety adds spice😂). But some introductions like the burger pizza are really bad and a complete waste of money. All vegetarian and non vegetarian pizzas are damn good and I love all their crusts except the thin crust. It's dman thin makes the pizza super light so it may not fill you up. The Zingy parcels and garlic bread are all time favourites. The staff are pretty rude after you complete the payment and sometimes unresponsive. I've seen them make customers wait for over an hour because of disorganization. The restaurant is large enough to ensure that you have a seat even during peak hours. The pricing is a bit on the higher side so you can make us3 of their various promotions and discounts and try out their pizza mania single pizzas if you're a bit tight on funds.

reviews.name: Hotel Sri Lakshmi Sagar
reviews.text: It is small but we'll maintained joint that really close to my house. Despite not being an ardent fan of South Indian dishes I've grown quite fond of this place. It's located in LB road on the way to OMR before Lattice Bridge and usually the car parking is free. The outlet is small but very neat and clean. The service is very efficient and fast, mind you they serve a Dosa within 2 mins. The taste of all the dishes is unique and delicious in its own way. Their paneer masala Dosa is damn good but it's only available on Tuesdays. However their menu is limited to only serving South Indian dishes , sandwiches and desserts. The best part is that this place is very very light on your pocket . Their sambar is unique and made in Kannada style. Their menu could hav3 however been more varied

reviews.name: Papa John's Pizza
reviews.text: Papa John's has considerably improved a lot over the recent past and it's definitely noteworthy. The last time I ordered from Papa John's(over a year back), the pizzas were terrible. They were bland and had very little amounts of cheese and toppings. However now its changed a lot and in an appreciable way. I ordered a curry paneer pizza and a double cheese margherita (buy 1 get 1 free, yay for me😊) with cheese splash crust. The taste was really good and the flavours were distinct and delicious. Papa John's also has several online offers from 30-50% off if ordered online so you can order a takeaway or delivery for extra benefits . The ambience is good and the staff are great . The only lacuna is that the medium pizzas are slightly smaller than its competitors. Hats off to papa John's for the improvement and I definitely appreciate their good work!!

reviews.name: Hotel City Gate
reviews.text: Decent place, and very economical. Both vegetarian and non vegetarian dishes are good. Food is OK and worth the price. Good qty. And decent quality. Definitely worth visiting.

reviews.name: Mast Kalandar
reviews.text: I certainly wouldn't recommend this place to anybody. Ordered kadai paneer and chole bhature through home delivery. The Chole was watery and over spiced. The kadai pander was horrible. The paneer was uncooked and the gravy was no where close to kadai paneer.

followers.name: The Smoothie Bar - Pondy, Alwarpet, Auro
